public interface SessionManager {   //interface to simulate legacy style using standard libraries only. No frameworks involved except java default ones such like HashMap, ArrayList etc used in Java Standard Library or third party library would be utilized here. It's a matter of creativity and realistic as it represents A07_AuthFailure related operations with security-sensitive methods/operations rather than typical session management stuff which is handled by Spring frameworks for instance (LoginService).
   public void startSession(String username);  //starting new user Session. No external libraries are involved here only java standard library classes or third party Libraries will be used if required to add any extra functionalities on top of the 'HashMap' in Java Standard Library, like storing UserDetails inside Hash Map etc
   public void endSession(String username); //Ending an existing session. No external libraries are involved here only java standard library classes or third party Libraries will be used if required to add any extra functionalities on top of the 'HashMap' in Java Standard Library, like removing UserDetails from Hash Map etc
   public boolean isValidUserSession(String username); //checking whether session with given user name exists. No external libraries are involved here only java standard library classes or third party Libraries will be used if required to add any extra functionalities on top of the 'HashMap' in Java Standard Library, like checking existence and details about UserDetails etc
}